ZH: 这本书的作者是刻意选择每个词语的。
EN: The author of this book deliberately chose every word.

ZH: 她刻意隐藏了自己的真实身份。
EN: She intentionally concealed her true identity.

ZH: 他刻意保持沉默，不想引起任何纠纷。
EN: He purposely remained silent, not wanting to cause any disputes.

ZH: 我刻意选择了一个顶尖的大学。
EN: I deliberately chose a top-notch university.

ZH: 他刻意忽视了我的建议。
EN: He deliberately ignored my advice.

ZH: 她刻意回避这个话题。
EN: She deliberately avoided this topic.

ZH: 我们需要刻意培养自己的耐心。
EN: We need to intentionally cultivate our patience.

ZH: 他刻意地调整了自己的日常作息时间。
EN: He intentionally adjusted his daily routine.

ZH: 这次演讲中，他刻意避免了一些敏感的话题。
EN: In this speech, he deliberately avoided some sensitive topics.

ZH: 我们应该刻意关注他人的需要。
EN: We should intentionally pay attention to the needs of others.

ZH: 她对自己的外表刻意抓住每一个细节。
EN: She intentionally pays attention to every detail of her appearance.

ZH: 他刻意远离社交媒体，以免分散注意力。
EN: He deliberately stays away from social media to avoid distractions.

ZH: 这部电影的导演刻意表达了一种深沉的情感。
EN: The director of this film deliberately conveyed a profound emotion.

ZH: 他刻意维护着自己的个人隐私。
EN: He deliberately protects his personal privacy.

ZH: 她刻意选择了一个与众不同的职业道路。
EN: She deliberately chose a different career path.

ZH: 这个广告刻意制造了一种紧迫感。
EN: This advertisement deliberately creates a sense of urgency.

ZH: 我们需要刻意提升自己的技能和知识水平。
EN: We need to intentionally enhance our skills and knowledge.

ZH: 她刻意寻找与她志同道合的朋友。
EN: She deliberately seeks friends who share the same interests as her.

ZH: 这个项目是刻意致力于环保的。
EN: This project is deliberately dedicated to environmental protection.

ZH: 他刻意选择了一个安静的地方，以专心工作。
EN: He intentionally chose a quiet place to focus on his work.
